rawIndexableTextContent: The entrypoint to styling the FlyerViewUI  Overview The default FlyerStyle is minimal and uses native styling where possible. As a result, users of the FlyerViewUI will want to create a custom style and apply that as a view modifier to the FlyerViewUI. A View extension simplifies passing the custom style to the UI:  Custom flyer styles can be created by adding to a FlyerStyle extension, and using the type-erased control styles: AnyButtonStyle, AnyPrimitiveButtonStyle, AnyTextFieldStyle, AnyToggleStyle. rawIndexableTextContent: The TCDigitalFlyerUI contains extensions and components to integrate the Transcontinental iOS SDK into a SwiftUI application, while also providing an easily themeable search and filter UI. Getting Started The instructions for installing and setting up the SDK are located in the Transcontinental iOS SDK repo. The instructions for using the SwiftUI extensions are below. Minimum Requirements XCode (>= 15.0) iOS (>= 15.0) Rendering a Publication The FlyerViewUI is a custom view that serves as the entry point for displaying the digital flyer in SwiftUI. It accepts the attributes of a publication to display, along with a style extension that governs its visual behaviour. The FlyerViewUI is otherwise a fully controlled component, managing its own functionality and API calls internally.  digitalFlyer - The provisioned instance of the DigitalFlyer to use attributes - The Publication.Attributes object returned from listPublications(storeId:language:date:completion:) event - A FlyerView.Event object that represents an event emitted by the FlyerView flyerStyle - A modifier that applies a custom style to the FlyerViewUI Styling the UI The default FlyerStyle is minimal and uses native styling where possible. As a result, users of the FlyerViewUI will want to create a custom style and apply that as a view modifier to the FlyerViewUI. A custom style is of the form of:  where Self represents the FlyerStyle initialization. A simple customization is shown below, where only the Mastheads logo is configured.  A fully custom style can be seen in the iOS demo application.
summary: The TCDigitalFlyerUI contains extensions and components to integrate the Transcontinental iOS SDK into a SwiftUI application, while also providing an easily themeable search and filter UI.
title: TCDigitalFlyerUI
